ZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"de140088bb7d6a8d01192f19f9cde75737b6e9a4ce2c30df7d6072ff2556856e","event_uuid":"1dddb500-e682-44d8-899d-70220a5d783a","position":{"commit_sha":"756c25c7917356b3b0f7dba4e43003cc751b1c2d","position":"1784759343642435001-1dddb500-e682-44d8-899d-70220a5d783a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"274a167a0c9557445bebf691dfaf3f2005a1922daea217fbe8b20a820c4b5d41","event_uuid":"f986d564-e74d-4dd1-b438-5f068333f9a1","position":{"commit_sha":"403483f9c5b16fce7bae495e2204dcefa7a9d13c","position":"1784759817204458501-f986d564-e74d-4dd1-b438-5f068333f9a1"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"b3ee85f1-444b-4969-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[],"created_at":1784695343772809001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"8fa2def1-fff0-4243-9540-222c4a4ca4d7","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"6673-7636-a116-4f90"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe final Jira modules still sit at the package root: `acli.py`, `acli_cli_ops.py`,\n`acli_graph.py`, `acli_rest.py`, `acli_subprocess.py`, `adf.py`, `outbound_fields.py`, and\n`comment_limits.py`. Per ADR 0035 §(c) the seam is `adapters/jira/`, so these belong under it.\nThis is the **last** story and it is atomic by necessity (ADR §1/§2): the three location-pinned\nmodules (`adf.py`, `outbound_fields.py`, `comment_limits.py`) break the file-location loader\nunless the loader is taught their new dir in the same change, and every surviving reference must\nmove together with no re-export shim (ADR Decision 4).\n\n**Prerequisite state.** S4 [rebar:6673-7636-a116-4f90] (a `depends_on` prerequisite of this\nstory) removes the *backend-neutral core's* direct imports of these modules by routing it\nthrough the `Backend` port. This story **assumes that landed state** and moves the now\nadapter-only files; the exact surviving reference set is re-confirmed by grep at implementation\ntime (it must not include any core module once S4 has landed).\n\nEdit-set (the references that survive S4 — verified against current `main`, to be re-confirmed\nafter S4 lands):\n- Physically move the eight modules into `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/`.\n- **Loader**, taught the new dir *without* breaking the ~30 other root modules it also loads:\n  `_loader.lazy_load(key, filename)` resolves `path = _PACKAGE_DIR / filename`\n  (`_loader.py:39,56`), so pass a **relative subpath** for the three moved location-pinned\n  modules. The exact by-path load sites for these three (grep-confirmed on current `main`, each a\n  module-local lazy-loader singleton — there is **no** `__main__.py` load site for them; `__main__.\n  _load_sibling_keyed` only loads `mode.py`/`_advisory_lock.py` and is untouched) are:\n  - `lazy_load(_ADF_KEY, \"adf.py\")` → `\"adapters/jira/adf.py\"` at **three** sites:\n    `outbound_fields.py:69`, `outbound_comments.py:84`, and `inbound_translate.py:323`\n    (`_ADF_KEY_APPLIER`).\n  - `lazy_load(_COMMENT_LIMITS_KEY, \"comment_limits.py\")` → `\"adapters/jira/comment_limits.py\"` at\n    `outbound_comments.py:100`.\n  - the `spec_from_file_location` site that loads `adf` by sibling path —\n    `inbound_fields.py:36–37` (`adf_path = Path(__file__).parent / \"adf.py\"`) → point at\n    `adapters/jira/adf.py` (also listed under the sibling-reference set below).\n  Each resolves correctly under the relative subpath and leaves all other root lookups untouched.\n  (`outbound_fields.py`, being itself one of the moved modules, moves with its `_ADF_KEY` loader\n  intact — its `lazy_load` call is repointed like the others.)\n- **Surviving intra-adapter / non-core references to repoint** (dotted + sibling-filename):\n  - `adapters/jira/jira_fields.py:18–24` — **two** dotted imports of moved modules, both\n    repointed: `from rebar_reconciler.adf import fit_text_to_adf_limit` (line `:18`) →\n    `from rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira.adf import fit_text_to_adf_limit`, **and** the\n    `from rebar_reconciler.comment_limits import _JIRA_COMMENT_MAX_CHARS` (lines `:19–21`) /\n    `from rebar_reconciler.comment_limits import truncate_comment_body` (lines `:22–24`) →\n    `from rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira.comment_limits import …` (all three targets now\n    co-located under `adapters/jira/`). Missing the `comment_limits` lines fails the module\n    import after the move.\n  - `inbound_fields.py:36` — `adf_path = Path(__file__).parent / \"adf.py\"` (the InboundMapper\n    impl stays at root; adf moved) → point at `adapters/jira/adf.py`.\n  - `acli.py:76` — `from rebar_reconciler.adf import text_to_adf as _text_to_adf` (moves with the\n    `acli*` cluster; becomes an intra-adapter import\n    `from rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira.adf import text_to_adf as _text_to_adf`). Omitting it\n    leaves a dangling root-path import that fails at runtime after the move.\n  - `acli_cli_ops.py:36` — `from rebar_reconciler.adf import …` (moves with the `acli*` cluster;\n    becomes an intra-adapter import).\n  - Any `outbound_comments.py` / `inbound_translate.py` / `reconcile_check.py` adf/comment_limits\n    loader refs **not already eliminated by S4** — grep-confirmed at S5 time; repoint or drop.\n- **Test surface** (characterized correctly — the first draft's \"~29 `mock.patch` strings\" was\n  wrong; there are **zero** `mock.patch(\"rebar_reconciler.acli…\")` string patches). Three\n  distinct categories:\n  1. ~23 files use `patch.object(applier|fetcher, \"_load_acli\", …)` — **object-level,\n     path-agnostic**; unaffected by the physical move (they inject a fake transport).\n  2. ~18 files hardcode `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location(…, \"<moved>.py\")` /\n     `SCRIPTS_DIR/… \"acli.py\"`-style **path constants** naming a moved module → must be rewritten\n     to the `adapters/jira/` path.\n  3. ~18 files use direct dotted imports `from rebar_reconciler.acli… / .adf / .outbound_fields`\n     → must be rewritten to `adapters.jira.*`.\n  Categories 2+3 (their deduped union) are the atomic migration set; category 1 is verified\n  still-green, not edited.\n\n## Approach\n\nOne atomic change (the constraints forbid a partial move). Re-run the grep sweep to enumerate\nevery surviving reference (categories above), move the files, teach the loader via relative\nsubpaths, repoint every dotted/sibling reference, and rewrite the category-2/3 test targets —\nthen run the full suite. The change is complete when a grep for the old root paths of the moved\nmodules returns zero hits in `src/` **and** `tests/` (excluding the path-agnostic `_load_acli`\npatches) and the suite is green. No behavior changes — a pure relocation + rebind.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Move the eight remaining Jira modules into `adapters/jira/`.\n- Relative-subpath loader updates for the three location-pinned modules.\n- Repoint every surviving dotted/sibling reference (incl. `jira_fields.py:18`,\n  `inbound_fields.py:36`, `acli_cli_ops.py:36`) and rewrite the category-2/3 test targets,\n  atomically, with no re-export shims.\n- **Out of scope:** any behavior change; the core rewire (S4, prerequisite); new backends\n  (epic `be74`). `jira_fields.py` already relocated in Phase 1 — only its `adf` import changes.\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Tier:** integration (full suite) + a structural gate.\n- **Full suite green** after the move is the primary oracle — the category-1 `_load_acli` tests\n  and the rewritten category-2/3 tests all exercise the moved modules at their new paths.\n- **Loader test:** dynamically loading `adf`/`outbound_fields`/`comment_limits` through the\n  reconciler entry point succeeds at the new location (staging the move without the loader edit\n  fails RED).\n- **Non-moved-consumer regression:** exercising `inbound_fields.py` (which loads `adf` by sibling\n  path) resolves the moved file, and the ~30 other root modules the loader serves are unaffected\n  (a root-module dynamic load still succeeds) — proving the relative-subpath change is scoped.\n- **Structural gate:** `grep` finds **zero** references to the old root paths of the moved\n  modules in `src/` and `tests/` (excluding the path-agnostic `_load_acli` `patch.object`\n  sites), and **no** re-export shim remains at any old path.\n- **Teeth:** leave one category-2 path constant at the old path and confirm that test errors.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The eight modules physically reside under `adapters/jira/`; no source file remains at\n  their old root paths and no re-export shim exists there — verified by `ls`/`grep`.\n- [ ] The loader resolves `adf` / `outbound_fields` / `comment_limits` at the new sub-package\n  path via relative subpaths, and a root-module dynamic load still succeeds (loader test +\n  non-moved-consumer regression).\n- [ ] Every surviving dotted/sibling reference is repointed (`jira_fields.py:18`,\n  `inbound_fields.py:36`, `acli_cli_ops.py:36`, and any S4-residual loader refs); the deduped\n  category-2/3 test targets reference the new `adapters.jira.*` paths — verified by `grep` for\n  the old targets returning zero hits (excluding the path-agnostic `_load_acli` patches).\n- [ ] Every `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/*.py` stays within the 800-LOC module-size cap\n  (`.github/module-size-limit.txt`) after the move — verified by the module-size gate.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all green.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/acli.py","reason":"Relocate acli* cluster + adf/outbound_fields/comment_limits under adapters/jira"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_loader.py","reason":"Relative-subpath resolution for moved location-pinned modules; no _PACKAGE_DIR change"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/__main__.py","reason":"_load_sibling_keyed / spec_from_file_location sites for moved modules"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py","reason":"inbound_fields.py:36 sibling adf.py path repointed to adapters/jira"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/jira_fields.py","reason":"jira_fields.py:18 adf import becomes intra-adapter"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/state/test_config_jira_wiring.py","reason":"Category-2/3 test target: dotted import + spec_from_file_location path rewrite"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","6673-7636-a116-4f90"],["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"5443e4ab-aa2d-4a0a-a7e0-b7cf52e0fa91","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["reconciler","vendor-adapter","relocation"],"ticket_id":"dfb9-d2d1-455d-48d9","ticket_type":"story","title":"Relocate acli*/adf/outbound_fields/comment_limits into adapters/jira/ + teach loader; migrate ~29 patch strings atomically","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["93964d75-31f8-482f-be93-d354f4c9e246","4ad1160f-4524-4511-ac84-4310f475c201","f4623077-c141-4759-bb15-cf3d04f4e6b9","8fa2def1-fff0-4243-9540-222c4a4ca4d7","c65d335f-e72b-404a-a1cf-92ec153a38ae","b431de17-1e52-4f1e-be81-c13972a826cc","36ba58ce-cbf1-4bf1-ac2b-cd70e49b0925","51f1b221-1c2d-44e6-8072-6e8ca8012e13","640e7855-f2db-4ce0-9b9